.\" generated from doc/git-hack.1.ronn — do not edit this file directly. Run: make man
.TH "GIT\-HACK" "1" "March 2026" "git-hack" "User Commands"
.
.SH "NAME"
\fBgit\-hack\fR \-\- AI\-augmented git workflow helper
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.
.nf
\fBgit hack\fR [\fIidea\-text\fR]
\fBgit hack idea\fR [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR] [\fIidea\-text\fR]
\fBgit hack issue\fR [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR] \fInumber\fR
\fBgit hack commit\fR [\-a] [\-A] [\-c] [\-p] [\-n] [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR]
\fBgit hack propose\fR [\-d] [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR]
\fBgit hack ship\fR [\-a] [\-c] [\-d] [\-n] [\-y] [\-m \fImodel\fR]
\fBgit hack pick\fR [\fIsha\fR] [\fIbranch\fR]
\fBgit hack pick\fR \-\-continue
\fBgit hack done\fR
\fBgit hack init\fR
.fi
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBgit\-hack\fR augments git workflows with AI assistance\. It uses the \fBllm\fR CLI to generate branch names, commit messages, and pull request descriptions, and \fBgit\-town\fR for branch lifecycle management\. Typical flow: create a branch with \fBidea\fR or \fBissue\fR, make changes, commit with \fBcommit\fR, open a PR with \fBpropose\fR, and clean up with \fBdone\fR\.
.
.P
When invoked without a subcommand, \fBgit hack\fR runs in interactive \fBidea\fR mode\. When invoked with an unrecognised first argument, that argument is treated as an idea description\.
.
.SH "SUBCOMMANDS"
.
.SS "idea (default)"
.
.nf
git hack [idea\-text]
git hack idea [\-y] [\-m model] [idea\-text]
.fi
.
.P
Generate a branch name from a free\-text description using \fBllm\fR, then create the branch via \fBgit town hack\fR\. Prompts interactively if \fIidea\-text\fR is omitted\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Accept the AI\-generated branch name without prompting\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.SS "issue"
.
.nf
git hack issue [\-y] [\-m model] <number>
.fi
.
.P
Fetch the title and body of a GitHub issue via \fBgh\fR, generate a branch name with \fBllm\fR, and create the branch via \fBgit town hack\fR\. Requires \fBgh\fR to be installed and authenticated (\fBgh auth login\fR)\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Accept the AI\-generated branch name without prompting\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.SS "commit"
.
.nf
git hack commit [\-a] [\-A] [\-c] [\-p] [\-n] [\-y] [\-m model]
.fi
.
.P
Generate a commit message for staged changes using \fBllm\fR and commit\. If no changes are staged, offers to run \fBgit add \-p\fR\.
.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-all\fR
Stage all tracked modifications (\fBgit add \-A\fR) before generating the message\.
.
.TP
\fB\-A\fR, \fB\-\-amend\fR
Amend the previous commit instead of creating a new one\. Implies \fB\-\-force\-with\-lease\fR when pushing\.
.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-conventional\fR
Generate a Conventional Commit subject (\fBtype: description\fR) instead of a plain imperative subject\.
.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-push\fR
Push to origin after committing\.
.
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-no\-verify\fR
Skip pre\-commit and commit\-msg hooks\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Commit with the AI message without prompting\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.SS "propose"
.
.nf
git hack propose [\-d] [\-y] [\-m model]
.fi
.
.P
Generate a PR title and body using \fBllm\fR, then open or update the pull request via \fBgit town propose\fR\.
.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-draft\fR
Open the PR as a draft\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Submit without confirming the generated title/body\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.SS "ship"
.
.nf
git hack ship [\-a] [\-c] [\-d] [\-n] [\-y] [\-m model]
.fi
.
.P
Run \fBcommit\fR then \fBpropose\fR in a single step\. Flags are forwarded to the appropriate subcommand: \fB\-n\fR (no\-verify) goes to \fBcommit\fR only; \fB\-d\fR (draft) goes to \fBpropose\fR only; all other flags go to both\.
.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-all\fR
Stage all tracked modifications before committing\.
.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-conventional\fR
Use Conventional Commit format for the commit message\.
.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-draft\fR
Open the resulting PR as a draft\.
.
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-no\-verify\fR
Skip pre\-commit and commit\-msg hooks during the commit step\.
.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Accept all AI suggestions without prompting\.
.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fImodel\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fImodel\fR
Override the default \fBllm\fR model for this invocation\.
.
.SS "pick"
.
.nf
git hack pick [sha] [branch]
git hack pick \-\-continue
.fi
.
.P
Cherry\-pick a commit onto the target branch\. When called without arguments, presents an interactive list of recent commits from the default base branch (uses \fBfzf\fR if available)\. After a successful pick, offers to push\.
.
.TP
\fB\-\-continue\fR
Resume a cherry\-pick that was paused due to conflicts\. Verifies that all conflicts are resolved and all files are staged before continuing\.
.
.SS "done"
.
.nf
git hack done
.fi
.
.P
Sync the current branch with its parent (\fBgit town sync\fR), delete the merged branch (\fBgit town delete\fR), and check out the main branch\. Fails if the branch has not been merged\.
.
.SS "init"
.
.nf
git hack init
.fi
.
.P
Install global git aliases into \fB~/\.gitconfig\fR:
.
.TS
allbox;
l l .
Alias	Expands to
\fBgit c\fR	\fBgit\-hack commit\fR
\fBgit cap\fR	\fBgit\-hack commit \-a \-p\fR
\fBgit pr\fR	\fBgit\-hack propose\fR
\fBgit propose\fR	\fBgit\-hack propose\fR
\fBgit pick\fR	\fBgit\-hack pick\fR
\fBgit done\fR	\fBgit\-hack done\fR
.TE
.
.SH "DEPENDENCIES"
.
.P
Required:
.
.TP
\fBgit\fR
Version control\.
.
.TP
\fBllm\fR
AI model CLI\. See \fIhttps://llm\.datasette\.io\fR\.
.
.TP
\fBgit\-town\fR
Branch lifecycle management\. See \fIhttps://www\.git\-town\.com\fR\.
.
.P
Optional:
.
.TP
\fBfzf\fR
Interactive fuzzy selection for \fBpick\fR and \fBidea\fR\.
.
.TP
\fBgh\fR
GitHub CLI, required for the \fBissue\fR subcommand\.
.
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
.
.P
Run once per repository to configure git\-town branch tracking:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf
git town config setup
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
Select the \fBllm\fR model to use:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf
llm models                          # list available models
llm \-m claude\-3\-5\-sonnet\-latest \&…  # use a specific model
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
The \fB\-m\fR / \fB\-\-model\fR flag on any subcommand overrides the model for a single invocation\.
.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
git(1), git\-town(1), llm(1), gh(1), fzf(1)
